What is Lipodissolve? Lipodissolve is a non-surgical alternative to liposuction to remove localised fat deposits that are resistant to diet and exercise. It is not used for weight loss but rather for body sculpting.

Does lipo dissolve work?
YES, lipodissolve does work! The studies say  lippodissolve is clinically effective at removing moderate amounts of fat in appropriate patients.

Does lipo dissolve tighten skin?
YES,  lipodissolve is highly effective in reducing unwanted deposits of localized fat and that it can tighten the skin to some extent,

How long does fat dissolving last?
The solution will dissolve the fat cells, which then undergo degradation and absorption by the body over a length of 4 - 6 weeks.

How many sessions needed for fat dissolving?
For the best results,. Most common is two to three treatments, spaced four to six weeks apart. But it’s not mandatory- your choice! 

What can go wrong with fat dissolving injections?
Side effects of both injectable treatments are rare. You may experience swelling, bruising, itching, a little pain pain, sensitivity to pressure and excessive warmth at the injection site however, this is usually resolved within three to five days.
